  "prompt": "How can I completely eliminate sweaty palms?",
  "response": "Eliminating sweaty palms, also known as palmar hyperhidrosis, can be challenging, but there are several approaches to manage and significantly reduce the issue. Here are some effective methods:\n\n1. **Lifestyle Changes:**\n   - **Reduce Stress and Anxiety:** Practice stress-reduction techniques like meditation, yoga, or deep-breathing exercises.\n   - **Dietary Adjustments:** Limit intake of caffeine, spicy foods, and alcohol, as these can trigger sweating.\n\n2. **Topical Treatments:**\n   - **Antiperspirants:** Use an over-the-counter antiperspirant containing aluminum chloride. For severe cases, prescription-strength versions like Drysol might be recommended by a doctor.\n\n3. **Medical Treatments:**\n   - **Iontophoresis:** This involves using a device that passes mild electrical currents through water and into the skin\u2019s surface, blocking the sweat glands temporarily.\n   - **Botox Injections:** Botulinum toxin injections can be used to block the nerves that cause sweating for several months.\n   - **Oral Medications:** Anticholinergic drugs can reduce sweating, but they may have side effects.\n\n4. **Surgical Options:**\n   - **Endoscopic Thoracic Sympathectomy (ETS):** A surgical procedure that cuts the nerves causing excessive sweating. This is typically considered only when other treatments have failed, due to the risk of compensatory sweating in other body areas.\n\n5. **Natural Remedies:**\n   - **Baking Soda and Cornstarch:** Mix equal parts and apply to the palms to absorb moisture.\n   - **Sage Tea Soak:** Soak hands in cooled sage tea, as it has natural astringent properties.\n\nBefore starting any treatment, it\u2019s advisable to consult with a healthcare professional to determine the most appropriate option for your situation.",
